On Wednesday, Prague&#39;s public transport will take the chip for the first time
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be recorded in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date when the first passengers will board the metro, trams and buses, who will have an electronic coupon in their pocket instead of a paper ticket.
At the moment, it can be purchased by about one hundred thousand people who own an Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a 30-day, a 90-day and an annual coupon (which will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time upload it to their chip card at the Transport Company&#39;s information centers and workplaces at Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany metro stations. Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
As of yesterday, coupons can also be purchased via the Internet on the Transport Company&#39;s website www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred customers used the service until the afternoon.
