One mysterious phenomenon has been causing confusion among scientists for years - the gravitational sling anomaly.
A gravitational slingshot is an aerial maneuver of space probes in which they gain additional momentum in the gravitational field of a cosmic body, such as the Earth.
As a result, the probes can save a lot of fuel.
The European-American Cassini-Huygens research probe used this physical trick in the same way as the Ulysses solar probe.
