The first of these phenomena is the reactualization, the extraordinary revival of the market, the double category of state-power in relation to a certain renationalization of the economy.
The crisis is indeed a crisis of banking and financial institutions, which, of course, have strong ties abroad, but which mainly involve the budgets of people and families living in a single country, in a single state.
